						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Bregalad wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Well, when people state something, it is by default their own opinion, unless explicitly mentioned otherwise.<br /></div>Nonetheless, it helps civil discourse to <em>stay</em> civil when people mark statements of their own opinion with such.<br /><br />&quot;$thing is ugly&quot; is an invitation for a stupid argument.<br />&quot;In my opinion, $thing is ugly&quot; reduces the incentive to engage in the stupid argument.</div>

