					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Shonumi basically echoes my reasoning for the design. I don't consider myself an actual sprite artist in the first place and worked with the 32-bit sprite as a reference as noted. I tried just color reducing the original sprite at first but the decrease in fidelity just looked too obvious and thought that could be mitgated by presenting something different. Plus, I did find the chibi head to be kinda offputting when I started thinking more about it and generally prefer the more &quot;realistic&quot; style of 16-bit characters with more implicit facial features.<br /><br />Anyway, I didn't really mean for this thread to turn into a pages long debate on the sprite itself.</div>

